about.summary: This package can be used to solve Linear Programming / Linear Optimization problems by using the simplex algorithm.

name: r-linprog
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.9-2' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-linprog
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/linprog_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/linprog/linprog_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 8937b2e30692e38de1713f1513b78f505f73da6f5b4a576d151ad60bac2221ce

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 2
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-lpsolve
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-lpsolve

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('linprog')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('linprog')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: http://linprog.r-forge.r-project.org/
  license: GPL (>= 2)
  summary: This package can be used to solve Linear Programming / Linear Optimization problems
    by using the simplex algorithm.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
